            <title>System Requirements</title>
            <paragraph>Swift development currently targets Ubuntu Server 14.04, but should work on
                most Linux platforms.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Swift is written in Python and has these dependencies:</paragraph>
            <bullet_list bullet="*">
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Python 2.7</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>rsync 3.0</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>The Python packages listed in <reference name="the requirements file" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/requirements.txt">the requirements file</reference><target ids="the-requirements-file" names="the\ requirements\ file" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/requirements.txt"></target></paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Testing additionally requires <reference name="the test dependencies" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/test-requirements.txt">the test dependencies</reference><target ids="the-test-dependencies" names="the\ test\ dependencies" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/test-requirements.txt"></target></paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph>Testing requires <reference name="these distribution packages" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/other-requirements.txt">these distribution packages</reference><target ids="these-distribution-packages" names="these\ distribution\ packages" refuri="https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/other-requirements.txt"></target></paragraph>
                </list_item>
            </bullet_list>
            <paragraph>There is no current support for Python 3.</paragraph>
